1
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:53,720
Tom, wait up.

2
00:00:54,719 --> 00:00:57,000
l heard about Megan. You doing okay?

3
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,400
Train's running in 10 minutes.

4
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,680
That's the thing
about this messed-up disease.

5
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:06,480
My mother-in-law, God rest her soul,
she was only 66.

6
00:01:07,039 --> 00:01:09,040
Megan's 42.

7
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,320
lt's about time, Hog Head.

8
00:01:12,479 --> 00:01:15,080
Car trouble. Sorry, Tom.

9
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:17,040
What do l care?

10
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:20,840
l got your train today.
It's all set with the boys upstairs.

11
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:25,600
Take some time off.
We got you covered.

12
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,920
l wanna work.

13
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:32,400
Wait up, Tom.

14
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:37,440
All right, l wanna tell you this
as a friend and not your boss, Tom.

15
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,280
You're not dealing with this.

16
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:42,480
l'm dealing with it, my way.

17
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:45,280
All right.
l'll give you all the streaks you want...

18
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:47,680
...but if you don't
spend time with her now...

19
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,160
.. .you're gonna regret it
the rest of your life.

20
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,800
Give him his orders.

21
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,760
See you, Tom.

22
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,560
How long do l have?

23
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,400
l can't answer that.

24
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,640
Well, give me your best bet.

25
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,040
l won't hold you to it.

26
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:43,200
-Are you all right, Megan?
-Oh, yeah. l'm fine.

27
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,600
Hey, what's the date today?

28
00:03:06,759 --> 00:03:08,480
Tuesday, February 2nd.

29
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:11,040
Tom, do you really think
you should be driving?

30
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:14,200
Don't you start with me too.

31
00:03:19,919 --> 00:03:24,000
This is Stargazer Express.
We are setting up and running.

32
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,480
Wanda, your favorite train is leaving.

33
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,880
About time. Stargazer Express.

34
00:03:29,039 --> 00:03:32,560
Come on, baby. Don't give us
a hard time over five little minutes.

35
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:34,200
Because you know you want me.

36
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,840
Like l want hemorrhoids.
Over and out. Romeo.

37
00:03:38,159 --> 00:03:39,600
Over and out.

38
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,880
-Romeo, huh?
-Yes, sir.

39
00:03:43,479 --> 00:03:46,120
Love on a train.
Man, there ain't nothing like it.

40
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:08,600
So. what do think about trains now?

41
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:12,680
l love trains.

42
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,560
l love you.

43
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:19,840
Tom? You done?

44
00:04:20,919 --> 00:04:22,400
Yeah, l'm done.

45
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,960
Welcome to the Stargazer Express.

46
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:46,920
We'll be taking you all the way to
Oakland. and from there. on to Seattle.

47
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:50,600
So sit back, relax, and enjoy the ride.

48
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,520
Why, hello, Davey.

49
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:10,000
How's your poor mother, bless her,
on this lovely Tuesday morning?

50
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:13,160
-She's okay.
-Up and around, is she?

51
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:15,560
Not yet. But soon.

52
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,680
You sure?
Better tell her to watch her step then...

53
00:05:18,839 --> 00:05:21,040
-...all that drinking.
-Okay, later, Mrs. Brown.

54
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,560
Breakfast is ready, Mom.

55
00:05:36,839 --> 00:05:39,360
Did you say your morning prayers?

56
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,200
Eat your eggs before they get cold.

57
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,200
No, sweetie, l don't want it.

58
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,360
Mom, you have to eat something.

59
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,600
Kneel, Davey.

60
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:54,440
l said my prayers.

61
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:57,120
Well, say them again, sweetie.

62
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,760
O God, come to my aid.

63
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:06,280
l can't hear you, sweetie.

64
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:10,200
O Lord, make haste to help me.

65
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:15,440
Glory be to the Father, and to the Son,
and to the Holy Spirit.

66
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,600
Hallelujah.

67
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:22,040
You know, it's after 10.

68
00:06:22,199 --> 00:06:24,720
You slept so hard,
l didn't wanna wake you.

69
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:26,920
l feel stronger.

70
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:30,800
l knew it. l told you you'd feel better.

71
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:35,200
How long before the train gets here,
sweetie?

72
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,320
Thirty minutes.

73
00:06:39,319 --> 00:06:40,840
We're gonna see the train?

74
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,800
Yeah, Davey.

75
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:44,240
You mean it?

76
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,760
We don't have to,
if you're not feeling well.

77
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,480
l'm fine, baby.

78
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,560
Here, that's two for you...

79
00:06:58,079 --> 00:07:00,280
...and three for me.

80
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:05,360
-What for?
-To make us happy, baby.

81
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,440
To make us happy.

82
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:30,000
Honey, can you get the phone,
please?

83
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,960
l got it, Mom.

84
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,120
Hello?

85
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,840
Hi. this is the principal
at Eastside Elementary School.

86
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,760
l'm calling because Davey
hasn't been in school.

87
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:44,160
Well, you see, his mother died.

88
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:49,440
Oh. l'm very sorry.
We weren't aware of that.

89
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:53,360
Please let us know
when he'll be back. all right?

90
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:55,480
Okay. Thank you.

91
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:00,240
Are you still taking classes?

92
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,200
-Yeah. Of course.
-Accounting 101 ?

93
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:07,080
lntermediate Accounting 3.

94
00:08:08,399 --> 00:08:11,520
l'm telling you, Tom, if you were smart,
you'd be going too.

95
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:15,080
Trains, l mean, l love it, man,
but it's a dying business.

96
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,400
Mom.

97
00:08:33,959 --> 00:08:35,560
Are you okay?

98
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,040
Yeah, l'm fine.

99
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,920
We'll wait, Davey.

100
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:48,640
-We'll wait until it comes, and then--
-Did you know the Stargazer Express...

101
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:50,520
...goes all the way to Seattle?

102
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,720
l love you, baby.

103
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:56,960
-Cold today.
-l know.

104
00:08:58,799 --> 00:09:00,040
Good morning, passengers.

105
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,520
We are approaching
beautiful Simi Valley.. .

106
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,920
...right on time.

107
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:08,040
O God, you are my God.

108
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:09,960
l wait for you from the dawn.

109
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,480
There's two engineers
on each passenger train.

110
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:15,440
My body longs for you.

111
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,480
Pray with me, baby.

112
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:21,920
-But l already prayed.
-Pray with me, Davey.

113
00:09:23,559 --> 00:09:26,000
My lips will praise you...

114
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,800
...for your mercy is better
than life itself.

115
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,520
lt's here.

116
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:40,560
Wait, Mom, don't go, it's coming.

117
00:09:49,159 --> 00:09:51,160
Mom, what are you doing?

118
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,840
Mom!

119
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,880
lt's time to rest now, baby.

120
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,760
-Mom. Mom, wake up.
-Be brave, honey.

121
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:59,400
lt's gonna be over soon, baby.

122
00:09:59,879 --> 00:10:02,920
Mom! The train's gonna come!

123
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,280
-Mom, wake up! What are you doing?
-lt's okay.

124
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:11,200
-Object on the tracks.
-What?

125
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,880
Objects on tracks. Call it in.

126
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:15,240
-Jesus Christ. Jesus Christ.
-Call it in!

127
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:16,880
All right, l'm slowing down.

128
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:19,280
This is Stargazer Express,
approaching Highway 6.

129
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,960
We have an object on tracks.
repeat, object on tracks.

130
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,320
Sixty-eight miles an hour.

131
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:25,560
Mom!

132
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,760
Mom!

133
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,720
Wake up!

134
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:36,000
Oh, my God.

135
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:39,080
-What's the speed?
-Fifty-five miles an hour.

136
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,840
Still too fast, man. We're still too fast.

137
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,680
-We gotta stop this train, man.
-No!

138
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,360
No, no, no!
You're not stopping the goddamn train!

139
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:48,400
What are you talking about?
We gotta try!

140
00:10:48,559 --> 00:10:50,520
We can't.
We got too many cars on the turn.

141
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:53,760
-We have to take the chance!
-Hands off! We're following procedure!

142
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:57,560
-Screw procedure, Tom!
-There's nothing we can do about it now!

143
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,280
There is nothing we can do!

144
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,400
Help! Someone help me!

145
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,200
What are you doing?

146
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:08,640
Mom! Mom! Get out!

147
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:12,000
Fifty miles per hour.

148
00:11:12,799 --> 00:11:14,320
-Oh, my God.
-Forty-eight.

149
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:17,280
-All right, brace for impact.
-Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

150
00:11:18,639 --> 00:11:19,640
Mom!

151
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,960
Perfect.

152
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:12,640
Thanks.

153
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,160
May l?

154
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,840
The railroad.

155
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:22,720
Are you a trainman?

156
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,120
You ever been on one?

157
00:12:29,399 --> 00:12:34,480
l don't know
if l should kiss you or slap you.

158
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,760
Repeat after me: l.

159
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:40,880
-l.
-Would like.

160
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:42,520
Would like.

161
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:45,120
To take you out sometime.

162
00:12:45,279 --> 00:12:47,800
To take you out sometime.
You'd go out with me?

163
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:51,680
Well, now that you've asked me
so nicely, why not?

164
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,320
Hey, Megan.

165
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:04,200
Whoa, whoa, what are you doing?

166
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,760
-What's going on?
-Okay.

167
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:10,640
-Jesus.
-l'm... .

168
00:13:10,879 --> 00:13:13,080
l'm planting flowers.

169
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:16,040
Well, not in your condition.
You can't do this kind of work.

170
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,800
Where's Tom? Oh, jeez. Hold on.

171
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,440
Okay, thanks.

172
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,920
l thought he was keeping
an eye on you.

173
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:27,600
Sometimes l think he can't stand
to be around me.

174
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:33,680
Here.
Just in case you change your mind.

175
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,360
lt's beautiful, isn't it?

176
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,640
The piano?

177
00:13:43,879 --> 00:13:47,520
-l ordered it.
-You're kidding me.

178
00:13:47,679 --> 00:13:49,240
Oh, Megan.

179
00:13:49,399 --> 00:13:52,720
l'm gonna learn how to play.
l've always wanted to learn.

180
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:54,960
Megan, you have to rest.

181
00:13:56,360 --> 00:14:02,320
Do not go gentle into that good night.
Rage. rage. rage

182
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:07,360
Against the dying of the light.

183
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,760
ls that what you're doing? Raging?

184
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:17,320
lt's a poem.
It's a Dylan Thomas poem.

185
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:23,240
-Do you want me to get that?
-Yeah. Thanks.

186
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:31,840
Stark residence.

187
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:36,400
No, no. It's not.
Who should l say is calling?

188
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,840
Oh, is he all right?

189
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,320
Yes.

190
00:14:45,879 --> 00:14:48,760
Yes. Thank you.

191
00:14:50,559 --> 00:14:52,800
Tom had an accident.

192
00:15:06,279 --> 00:15:09,080
Give your specimen samples
to this officer.

193
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:12,280
Cheers. Let me know if l'm pregnant.

194
00:15:19,399 --> 00:15:21,800
Visual clearance coming
off the corner was 300 feet.

195
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:26,000
lf you do the math, the posted was 60,
figure it was between 50 and 45, but....

196
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,160
lt was a suicide.

197
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:33,240
No doubt about it.
We did everything by the book.

198
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:35,760
-The box will tell you that.
-We know you did, Tom.

199
00:15:35,919 --> 00:15:37,960
lt's just a complicated situation.

200
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:42,280
lt's a suicide. It's not complicated.

201
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,840
Not when there's a woman
and a young child involved.

202
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,640
We're bringing you on the carpet.

203
00:15:46,799 --> 00:15:50,320
Some whack-job
drives a car in front of my train.. .

204
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:53,360
-...and it's my fault?
-We don't have a choice on this one.

205
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:56,400
No one remembers Victor Lopez,
but everybody knows Susan Smith.

206
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:59,240
-What the hell's that supposed to mean?
-Victor Lopez.

207
00:15:59,399 --> 00:16:02,120
lt's the homeless man
who dove under my train in Oxnard.

208
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:05,760
Tom, nobody cares if some wacko
throws himself under a train...

209
00:16:05,919 --> 00:16:08,640
.. .but everybody feels
for a mother and her child.

210
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,800
Wait, Tom, look.
Look, l'll talk to him. Hold up, Tom.

211
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,840
Hey, it's a week, 10 days max,
you know?

212
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,600
Take time off. Give us a chance...

213
00:16:16,759 --> 00:16:19,360
-...to prove you did everything right.
-You know we did.

214
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,760
You know this is a formality, Tom.

215
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:24,560
We gotta do this.

216
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:28,080
l'm sorry, excuse me.
This way, this way. Excuse me.

217
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,760
You didn't stop.

218
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,840
You didn't stop.

219
00:16:35,759 --> 00:16:37,520
Hi. Are you okay?

220
00:16:37,679 --> 00:16:39,680
-Yeah, l'm all right.
-What happened?

221
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,760
Taking some time off.

222
00:16:41,919 --> 00:16:44,920
-They're making you?
-You saw the doctor?

223
00:16:47,559 --> 00:16:50,000
-Susan brought some soup over.
-Not hungry.

224
00:16:50,559 --> 00:16:52,720
You have to do chemo again?

225
00:16:54,399 --> 00:16:57,520
You know, this room, the kitchen?

226
00:16:58,799 --> 00:17:01,480
lt's my favorite room
in the whole house.

227
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,560
The only room we fully unpacked.

228
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,640
Yeah. What did the doctor say, Meg?
What are the options?

229
00:17:07,639 --> 00:17:09,680
We don't have any options.

230
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:13,520
l have days, weeks, maybe months.

231
00:17:16,519 --> 00:17:19,120
The cancer has metastasized
to my bones.

232
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:24,320
So we'll treat it again.
It's gonna be hard, but--

233
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,960
lt's over.

234
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:30,400
What are you talking about?
No, no, no. We gotta fight this. We--

235
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:32,800
l'm done fighting, Tom.

236
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:37,200
The chemo made me sick,
and the cancer's too advanced.

237
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:40,160
l don't wanna spend the rest of my life
in a hospital room...

238
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:42,560
...full of tubes and syringes
and oncologists.

239
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:45,760
-Come on, there's gotta be something.
-There's nothing.

240
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,680
We have to. We gotta try.
l mean, we gotta try to....

241
00:17:49,839 --> 00:17:53,200
Gotta try to find a way to deal,
you know, with--

242
00:17:53,359 --> 00:17:54,920
Death.

243
00:17:56,839 --> 00:17:58,200
Say it.

244
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:22,760
You know what, this is only for tonight.
Tomorrow, we'll find you a good home.

245
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:26,240
Okay? You don't feel tired?

246
00:18:27,559 --> 00:18:30,800
You need to get a little bit of sleep
if you can.

247
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:34,640
Good night, David.

248
00:18:36,759 --> 00:18:38,120
Okay.

249
00:18:57,359 --> 00:19:01,000
Well, maybe now that you have
some time off...

250
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,920
...maybe we can go to San Francisco.

251
00:19:06,359 --> 00:19:10,040
There's gonna be a hearing.
l have to be around to find out when.

252
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,200
Great.

253
00:19:13,359 --> 00:19:15,760
An official excuse.

254
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,400
No, it's not an excuse.

255
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:21,480
lf l'm absent at the hearing,
l'll lose my job.

256
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,440
You're like sand, Tom.

257
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:29,960
Harder l try to hold onto you,
the faster you slip through my fingers.

258
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,920
Okay.

259
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,880
lt's okay.

260
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,960
No.

261
00:20:41,599 --> 00:20:43,000
Out.

262
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,440
Meggie?

263
00:21:11,839 --> 00:21:14,200
Tom thinks that we can help you.

264
00:21:14,359 --> 00:21:16,720
He was very convincing
over the phone.

265
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,680
Well, we're a center
for alternative approaches...

266
00:21:19,839 --> 00:21:22,000
...to treat or ameliorate disease.

267
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:27,920
We offer applied kinesiology,
cupping, even electromagnetic therapy.

268
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,640
Can you cure me?

269
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:35,280
As a professional in the medical field,
you know that there are no guarantees.

270
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,760
However, we can try
to rejuvenate your system...

271
00:21:40,359 --> 00:21:43,600
...teach you a number
of relaxation techniques...

272
00:21:43,759 --> 00:21:47,120
...such as meditation,
deep breathing, self-hypnosis.

273
00:21:47,279 --> 00:21:49,800
All of these will help you relax.

274
00:21:50,319 --> 00:21:52,320
l don't wanna relax.

275
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,200
-l wanna live.
-Honey....

276
00:21:54,359 --> 00:21:56,320
Why don't we just
hear what she has to say.

277
00:21:56,480 --> 00:22:00,000
lt's all right, Tom.
Of course you wanna live, Megan.

278
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,880
And l would like to spend
what little is left of my life...

279
00:22:03,039 --> 00:22:04,760
...doing exactly what l want to do...

280
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:08,480
...which does not include
electromagnetic therapy.

281
00:22:11,519 --> 00:22:13,880
Okay. Thank you.

282
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:20,160
-You're not even listening to me.
-What do you want?

283
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:22,720
-What would you like me to do?
-What happened to us?

284
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,840
-What are you talking about?
-You heard me.

285
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,680
-Meggie, come on.
-Don't ''Meggie'' me.

286
00:22:26,839 --> 00:22:29,000
-l'm not some fragile thing.
-What do you want?

287
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,760
l wanna know why
we never had children. How about that?

288
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:35,320
l don't know, because we never found
the time. We never found the time.

289
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,560
How could we have time?

290
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,280
We moved in 10 different houses
in 1 5 years of marriage.

291
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,520
l'm a trainman.
That's what trainmen do.

292
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,960
That is not what trainmen do,
that's what you did.

293
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:47,720
That's not what trainmen do.
It's not the rules for trainmen.

294
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:52,080
How could anybody, anybody,
have a child like that?

295
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,160
You got sick.

296
00:22:58,279 --> 00:23:00,560
You're blaming me?

297
00:23:04,759 --> 00:23:06,880
No, l'm not blaming anyone.

298
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:09,760
lt was just the way things worked out.

299
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:31,720
l thought l had all this time...

300
00:23:32,559 --> 00:23:36,000
...to be a woman.

301
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:38,920
To be a wife...

302
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:44,120
...and a nurse, and a mother.

303
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:48,800
Then l found out l didn't. l just didn't.

304
00:23:49,039 --> 00:23:50,960
l don't have any time.

305
00:23:53,119 --> 00:23:56,160
l probably would have made
a lousy father, anyway.

306
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,800
l'm not afraid to die.

307
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:04,520
But to think that l haven't lived?

308
00:24:08,119 --> 00:24:10,240
That terrifies me.

309
00:24:12,839 --> 00:24:15,560
Thank you so much
for agreeing to do this so quickly.

310
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,640
You will be gentle with him,
though, Judy?

311
00:24:17,799 --> 00:24:19,920
l think he suffers from PTSD.

312
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,160
These kids don't need pity.

313
00:24:22,519 --> 00:24:25,400
They require structure and discipline.
That's my gift to them.

314
00:24:25,559 --> 00:24:28,880
-Right, it's just that his mother was--
-Now, stop. You already told me.

315
00:24:29,039 --> 00:24:33,320
Separate yourself from your job, Renee.
They're not your children.

316
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,080
Of course. You're right.

317
00:24:37,759 --> 00:24:39,120
Thanks.

318
00:24:45,039 --> 00:24:47,280
lt's a nice room, huh?

319
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:54,360
Well, it's a little pink, but at least
you have it all to yourself, right?

320
00:24:54,519 --> 00:24:57,440
lt's definitely better
than temporary boarding.

321
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:01,840
l don't wanna stay here.

322
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,720
This is gonna be a great place for you,
David.

323
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:07,160
Please don't make me stay.

324
00:25:07,319 --> 00:25:09,320
-You're gonna be safe.
-Please.

325
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:12,400
Honey, you'll be safe,
and l think you'll really like Judy.

326
00:25:12,559 --> 00:25:17,520
You let her know if you need anything,
and she'll get in touch with me, all right?

327
00:25:21,519 --> 00:25:22,640
Bye.

328
00:25:42,599 --> 00:25:44,880
Used to be my girl's room.

329
00:25:46,759 --> 00:25:48,840
We asked for a girl...

330
00:25:49,839 --> 00:25:51,440
...but you were an emergency.

331
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:55,160
You want some clean clothes?

332
00:26:03,079 --> 00:26:04,720
This'll have to do for now.

333
00:26:11,279 --> 00:26:13,160
We'll talk later.

334
00:26:15,599 --> 00:26:18,960
And it cleans for months.
Never scrub your toilet again.

335
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:21,960
Authorities have just revealed
the identity of the woman.. .

336
00:26:22,119 --> 00:26:26,720
...that was killed in the Simi Valley
train crash as 27-year-old Laura Danner.

337
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,440
The police say that her 1 1-year-old son.
David Danner.. .

338
00:26:29,599 --> 00:26:31,200
...had been with her in the car...

339
00:26:31,359 --> 00:26:34,960
.. .but he somehow managed
to escape the accident unharmed.

340
00:26:35,119 --> 00:26:39,120
l'm told that the senior engineer
who was driving that train. Tom Stark.. .

341
00:26:39,279 --> 00:26:42,960
.. .and his partner. Otis Higgs.
have been suspended pending--

342
00:26:43,119 --> 00:26:45,520
Kitchen is off-limits
between mealtimes.

343
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:48,680
TV privileges are permission only.
Understood?

344
00:26:48,839 --> 00:26:50,680
-Yes.
-''Yes, ma'am. ''

345
00:26:50,839 --> 00:26:53,480
As long as you live here,
you'll play by my rules.

346
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,120
Listen to your own rules.

347
00:26:56,279 --> 00:26:57,760
Go to your room.

348
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,480
You're the one
who should stay out of the kitchen.

349
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,520
You're bad.
l knew it the moment l saw you.

350
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:06,080
Get to your room. Now.

351
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,600
Go.

352
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,760
Get dressed and go to sleep.

353
00:28:24,079 --> 00:28:25,520
Hello?

354
00:28:30,519 --> 00:28:34,000
Hello? Anybody here?

355
00:28:43,279 --> 00:28:45,080
l fancy they're long gone.

356
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:49,200
The officers.
They collected their evidence and left.

357
00:28:50,039 --> 00:28:51,320
You knew them?

358
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,720
Laura and Davey? l suppose so.

359
00:28:58,119 --> 00:29:00,480
You look a bit pale, dearie.

360
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:03,880
-l do feel a little....
-Come on. Let me get you a cup of tea.

361
00:29:05,839 --> 00:29:08,640
Tom? Where are you?

362
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:10,440
l'm out in the garage.

363
00:29:11,519 --> 00:29:15,160
Hey, man, l'm sorry to disturb you
at the house, but....

364
00:29:19,279 --> 00:29:21,840
l had no idea you were
into model trains. This is nice.

365
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:26,160
Hey, man, you mind
if we go get a beer or something?

366
00:29:27,359 --> 00:29:28,800
Yeah, sure.

367
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,080
Let me get my coat.

368
00:29:36,559 --> 00:29:38,080
We'll let it brew a while.

369
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,400
-You're very kind.
-Now.. .

370
00:29:40,759 --> 00:29:42,920
...l've lived in this building five years.

371
00:29:43,079 --> 00:29:45,440
Now, Laura and l,
we were never bosom buddies...

372
00:29:45,599 --> 00:29:48,240
...but you don't live
that long next door to someone...

373
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,800
...without getting to know
them on an intimate level.

374
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:53,160
So did she ever mention suicide
to you?

375
00:29:53,799 --> 00:29:55,760
Oh, you are a nosy one.

376
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,560
Poking and snooping.

377
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,640
Now, how did you find us?
Who sent you?

378
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:01,840
-lt's listed in....
-Well, dear, dear, dear.

379
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:05,200
-Call information if you don't believe me.
-Trying times indeed, huh?

380
00:30:05,359 --> 00:30:06,800
Oh, cookies!

381
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,680
No, thank you.

382
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,960
Really.

383
00:30:13,119 --> 00:30:14,640
So you were saying, about Laura.

384
00:30:14,799 --> 00:30:17,280
Oh, yeah. Bless her.

385
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:20,080
l looked after the boy
here and there, you know.

386
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:25,640
Couldn't help but notice the men
coming and going from her apartment.

387
00:30:25,799 --> 00:30:27,640
l mean,
haven't been anybody for ages.

388
00:30:27,799 --> 00:30:30,200
But they used to flock
around her like hungry birds.

389
00:30:30,359 --> 00:30:31,960
But they stopped coming?

390
00:30:32,119 --> 00:30:34,000
Well, she had a breakdown.

391
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,800
Nerves disease.

392
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:38,880
Monstrous, really,
the tricks our mind plays on us.

393
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:42,440
Well, l used to drop by, do chores.

394
00:30:42,599 --> 00:30:43,800
Cook for the boy.

395
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:47,280
But frankly,
she needed professional help.

396
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,040
Tea?

397
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,240
So she gave up.

398
00:30:53,839 --> 00:30:55,920
ls that why you think she did it?

399
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,760
l really don't know.

400
00:31:00,799 --> 00:31:03,120
-Have you thought about it?
-About what?

401
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,120
The accident.

402
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,600
l'm just....

403
00:31:07,759 --> 00:31:10,000
l'm having a little bit
of a hard time with it.

404
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:14,160
Yeah, l-- l don't wanna talk about it.

405
00:31:14,319 --> 00:31:17,880
Look, l'm-- l'm gonna talk to N.B.

406
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:21,000
l'm gonna give him my notice.

407
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:25,280
No, you-- You can't do that. That makes
it look like we did something wrong.

408
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,680
-That's because we did.
-We didn't have a choice.

409
00:31:27,839 --> 00:31:30,040
-We didn't?
-No.

410
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:31,880
lf we'd used that emergency brake...

411
00:31:32,039 --> 00:31:34,520
.. .wheels could've flattened,
train could've derailed.

412
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:36,680
-We'll never know--
-We're not gonna know.. .

413
00:31:36,839 --> 00:31:39,840
...but-- But it was a judgment call,
and l-- l made it.

414
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,680
We killed a human being.

415
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,440
A person, Tom. l don't know...

416
00:31:45,079 --> 00:31:46,440
...how l can....

417
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:49,520
lt was a suicide.

418
00:31:53,839 --> 00:31:55,440
Suicide.

419
00:31:58,119 --> 00:32:01,360
You know, the homeless man
was my first one? Victor Lopez?

420
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:04,280
Come on, come on.
Can we talk about something else?

421
00:32:04,839 --> 00:32:07,360
lt was right before
the end of the run and....

422
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:10,800
l mean, we had a smooth ride
going for like 10 hours.

423
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:16,760
And then l see him. l mean, he's
standing on the tracks, clear as day.

424
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,400
And l'm blowing the horn. l'm--

425
00:32:18,559 --> 00:32:21,120
l'm ringing the bell.
l mean, l'm doing everything.

426
00:32:22,799 --> 00:32:24,720
He just ignored us.

427
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,840
They turn us into executioners.

428
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,960
You know what he did
right before we hit him?

429
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,440
He smiled at us.

430
00:32:38,799 --> 00:32:41,760
He had a death wish, you know?

431
00:32:42,799 --> 00:32:44,480
Some people do.

432
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,880
Other people don't wanna die,
they die anyway.

433
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,920
l'm gonna wait
till the hearing's done...

434
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:55,920
...but l'm giving my notice.

435
00:32:56,079 --> 00:32:57,480
Yeah, fine. Go ahead, do that.

436
00:32:57,640 --> 00:33:01,000
-Come on, man. Don't be an asshole.
-Because l got no time for a quitter.

437
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,920
You know what your problem is?

438
00:33:04,119 --> 00:33:07,720
Everything is dying around you and you
just can't deal with it, can you?

439
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,320
Hey! Hey, get out!

440
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:13,040
Get out! Now! Let's go!

441
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,760
Get out!

442
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,840
Talk about my wife again, l'll kill you.

443
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,600
You know what? Fuck you, Tom!
At least l'm alive.

444
00:33:26,759 --> 00:33:29,160
You're dead inside
and everybody knows it!

445
00:33:43,839 --> 00:33:45,040
What are you doing?

446
00:33:49,039 --> 00:33:53,680
l'm leaving for San Francisco,
tomorrow, alone.

447
00:33:53,839 --> 00:33:56,920
No, just wait...

448
00:33:57,079 --> 00:34:00,520
...wait until after the hearing
and l'll come with you.

449
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:02,080
No, you won't.

450
00:34:03,359 --> 00:34:06,440
You'll-- You'll sign up
for more train trips.

451
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:09,360
Come on, Meg,
Iet me make it up to you.

452
00:34:12,559 --> 00:34:13,960
What for?

453
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,280
A final goodbye?

454
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,640
Good night.

455
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,960
-Are you the conductor?
-Yes.

456
00:35:31,119 --> 00:35:33,360
l'm looking for my Uncle Tom.

457
00:35:33,519 --> 00:35:36,160
Yeah, l've seen him in this cab.
This is his train.

458
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:39,520
You mean Tom Stark?
l didn't know he had relatives.

459
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,840
Yeah. He has a sister.

460
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:46,800
Sorry, kid, but Tom's not on duty today.
He's off because of the accident.

461
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:51,760
Well, actually, l don't think
l have the right address.

462
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:53,960
You want me to check his address?

463
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:57,040
Could you hurry?
My mom's waiting in the car.

464
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,680
You're bossy.

465
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:03,040
You're just like your uncle.

466
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,960
l'll just wait right here.

467
00:36:06,719 --> 00:36:08,640
Are you ready to say you're sorry?

468
00:37:03,559 --> 00:37:05,000
What happened?

469
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:08,880
Don't go.

470
00:37:13,519 --> 00:37:15,200
l have to.

471
00:37:18,719 --> 00:37:21,600
What's gonna happen if you get worse?
l mean...

472
00:37:22,199 --> 00:37:27,320
.. .who's--?
Who's gonna take care of you there?

473
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:30,760
l'll figure it out.

474
00:37:36,559 --> 00:37:38,240
Please don't go.

475
00:37:38,719 --> 00:37:41,040
Please. l'm sorry.

476
00:37:41,679 --> 00:37:43,240
Please.

477
00:38:03,159 --> 00:38:05,520
Okay, l'll notify the police, Judy.

478
00:38:05,679 --> 00:38:06,960
Thanks.

479
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:11,920
Crap.

480
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:28,240
l can't do this.

481
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,680
lt's too late, Tom. Come on.

482
00:38:41,679 --> 00:38:43,080
-You didn't stop!
-Hey!

483
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,600
-Hey!
-What?

484
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:47,000
-What are you doing? Hey!
-Stop! All right, stop.

485
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:48,680
Get off me, kid.

486
00:38:49,159 --> 00:38:50,480
He killed my mom!

487
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:54,000
Tom! Don't hurt him!

488
00:38:54,159 --> 00:38:55,400
-What are you, nuts?
-Stop!

489
00:38:55,559 --> 00:38:57,720
l didn't kill your mother,
she killed herself!

490
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,760
-Will you stop it!
-No, she didn't!

491
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:03,040
How fast were you going?
Sixty? Seventy?

492
00:39:03,199 --> 00:39:06,000
-l was going 48.
-You didn't even try to stop!

493
00:39:06,199 --> 00:39:07,680
l don't owe you an explanation!

494
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:10,520
-Hey, Tom, stop it. Sweetie.
-Yes, you do!

495
00:39:10,679 --> 00:39:13,600
-Stop it!
-You could've stopped! You didn't try!

496
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,760
-You didn't even try!
-Listen, come on.

497
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:17,080
Okay, come on.

498
00:39:17,239 --> 00:39:20,000
-He killed my mother.
-Your mother killed herself.

499
00:39:20,159 --> 00:39:22,560
Come sit down. Let's have some water.
Come on.

500
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,960
-lt doesn't say.
-Yes, it does.

501
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:32,720
Show him where.

502
00:39:33,039 --> 00:39:36,120
Page 55, code 343.

503
