01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:10,480
The hearing's in five days.

770
01:06:15,239 --> 01:06:17,360
ln five days what?

771
01:06:17,679 --> 01:06:19,480
lt's the official hearing.

772
01:06:19,639 --> 01:06:23,640
lt's when they'll decide
whether Tom did the right thing...

773
01:06:24,000 --> 01:06:25,840
...in the accident.

774
01:06:27,159 --> 01:06:30,000
What if they decide
he didn't do the right thing?

775
01:06:30,159 --> 01:06:32,360
He won't be an engineer anymore.

776
01:06:32,519 --> 01:06:38,240
lt's okay. Tom is capable.
He can do a lot of different things.

777
01:06:38,960 --> 01:06:42,000
But there's nothing like running a train.

778
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:46,640
Go on.

779
01:06:51,440 --> 01:06:53,320
What do you call this one?

780
01:06:53,480 --> 01:06:56,520
That's the Atlas 3086.

781
01:06:57,840 --> 01:07:01,080
-lt's really nice.
-Yeah, thanks.

782
01:07:03,760 --> 01:07:06,960
l could tell them she wanted to die.

783
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:09,720
What?

784
01:07:11,280 --> 01:07:14,000
You could say it at your trial.

785
01:07:16,239 --> 01:07:21,680
No, it's a hearing. It's not a trial.
It's all right. Thanks.

786
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:25,000
You don't want me to tell them?

787
01:07:27,280 --> 01:07:30,480
lt doesn't really matter
if your mom wanted to die or not.

788
01:07:30,639 --> 01:07:34,000
The only thing that matters
is if l handled the situation correctly.

789
01:07:34,719 --> 01:07:35,760
l forgive you.

790
01:07:40,519 --> 01:07:42,360
You forgive me for what?

791
01:07:44,719 --> 01:07:47,760
She took away my options
when she put her car on the tracks.

792
01:07:49,760 --> 01:07:51,440
Yeah, she did.

793
01:07:51,880 --> 01:07:54,320
lt just so happens she chose my train.

794
01:07:57,079 --> 01:07:58,320
l know.

795
01:08:14,840 --> 01:08:15,960
l got zero.

796
01:08:16,119 --> 01:08:17,320
-No sick days?
-None.

797
01:08:17,480 --> 01:08:19,720
Excuse me. Hi, l was wondering
if you could help.

798
01:08:19,880 --> 01:08:24,400
Well, what is a pretty girl like you
doing in a train station all alone?

799
01:08:24,559 --> 01:08:27,360
Well, l'm looking for a missing boy.
Maybe you've seen him.

800
01:08:27,519 --> 01:08:29,400
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
We saw this guy, right?

801
01:08:29,560 --> 01:08:31,480
-When did we see him?
-Yeah. He just left.

802
01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:34,520
He was riding a horse,
and he said Darth Vader was his father.

803
01:08:34,680 --> 01:08:35,960
-Yeah--
-Yeah, thanks a lot.

804
01:08:36,119 --> 01:08:38,720
Wait, wait, wait. Let me see that.

805
01:08:42,159 --> 01:08:44,120
This is Tom's nephew.

806
01:08:44,279 --> 01:08:45,800
-No.
-Yeah.

807
01:08:45,960 --> 01:08:47,440
Who's Tom?

808
01:08:52,800 --> 01:08:57,160
He said he forgave me
for killing his mom.

809
01:09:01,600 --> 01:09:04,400
lt used to be so simple, you know?

810
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:10,160
Black and white.
There was a right thing to do...

811
01:09:10,319 --> 01:09:12,520
...and a wrong thing to do.

812
01:09:14,920 --> 01:09:18,480
Life is more like a gray area, Tom.

813
01:09:25,800 --> 01:09:27,440
Not everything.

814
01:09:28,479 --> 01:09:30,720
Some things you know for certain.

815
01:09:54,560 --> 01:09:56,320
Meggie.

816
01:09:56,479 --> 01:09:58,160
Hey, what's wrong?

817
01:09:58,760 --> 01:10:00,240
She's fine.

818
01:10:13,319 --> 01:10:14,760
Here.

819
01:10:39,720 --> 01:10:41,920
-The lady from Child Services.
-What?

820
01:10:42,479 --> 01:10:45,360
-She's at the door.
-lt's all right. Stay here.

821
01:10:52,680 --> 01:10:53,680
Who?

822
01:10:53,840 --> 01:10:55,640
The woman who put me
in the foster home.

823
01:10:58,960 --> 01:11:01,080
-Oh, hi. Tom Stark?
-Yeah.

824
01:11:01,239 --> 01:11:05,080
Hi, l'm Renee Hargrove.
Ventura Children and Family Services.

825
01:11:05,239 --> 01:11:09,200
We didn't actually meet, but l remember
seeing you at the scene of the accident.

826
01:11:09,359 --> 01:11:11,440
Would you mind if l came in?

827
01:11:14,199 --> 01:11:15,600
Sure.

828
01:11:16,079 --> 01:11:17,520
Thank you.

829
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:22,480
This is a lovely home.

830
01:11:25,079 --> 01:11:29,560
l am looking for a missing boy.
David Danner?

831
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:31,680
l know who he is.

832
01:11:32,479 --> 01:11:36,040
-Have you seen him since the accident?
-No.

833
01:11:36,439 --> 01:11:37,880
Really?

834
01:11:40,840 --> 01:11:43,760
Oh, l forgot the book.

835
01:11:46,199 --> 01:11:47,800
Oh, this is a great book.

836
01:11:47,960 --> 01:11:51,800
-Do you have children, Mr. Stark?
-That's my wife's.

837
01:11:53,640 --> 01:11:57,520
Would you mind terribly if l just took
a little look around? Do you mind?

838
01:11:57,680 --> 01:12:00,280
-Well--
-Thank you.

839
01:12:01,560 --> 01:12:04,560
David ran away from his foster home.

840
01:12:05,680 --> 01:12:08,280
So, what's that to me?

841
01:12:08,439 --> 01:12:11,520
Oh, Mr. Howie Pugh,
the train conductor.

842
01:12:11,680 --> 01:12:14,840
He told me that David
was on the train looking for you.

843
01:12:15,000 --> 01:12:17,160
He claimed to be your nephew.

844
01:12:17,640 --> 01:12:19,360
My nephew?

845
01:12:24,039 --> 01:12:25,520
Do you mind?

846
01:12:25,680 --> 01:12:30,760
Yeah, actually l do.
l mean, this is my home.

847
01:12:30,920 --> 01:12:34,280
l'm sorry. l know this is an imposition.

848
01:12:34,439 --> 01:12:38,880
Okay, you should go in here.
Go in here. Just be quiet.

849
01:12:42,239 --> 01:12:45,560
Excuse me,
l don't think you heard what l said.

850
01:12:45,720 --> 01:12:49,280
Tom? What's going on?

851
01:12:49,439 --> 01:12:50,960
My wife, Megan.

852
01:12:53,039 --> 01:12:56,880
Oh, l'm sorry to barge in like this,
but l'm looking for a missing boy.

853
01:12:58,520 --> 01:13:00,280
Yes, and l couldn't help but notice...

854
01:13:00,439 --> 01:13:02,960
...that the walls
in this room smell freshly painted...

855
01:13:03,279 --> 01:13:05,280
...and there's a little toy train.

856
01:13:08,960 --> 01:13:12,120
-You okay?
-She's sick.

857
01:13:15,520 --> 01:13:19,920
l have cancer, stage four.

858
01:13:20,079 --> 01:13:21,680
lt's in my bones.

859
01:13:22,199 --> 01:13:25,640
This is the spare room.
l have trouble sleeping.

860
01:13:25,800 --> 01:13:28,560
At night l come in here...

861
01:13:28,720 --> 01:13:32,720
...because l don't wanna disturb
my husband.

862
01:13:32,920 --> 01:13:35,280
He's just painted it for me...

863
01:13:36,720 --> 01:13:39,760
...because blue is my favorite color.

864
01:13:41,520 --> 01:13:44,760
-l'm sorry.
-You said that already.

865
01:13:46,720 --> 01:13:48,920
Do you want to look around?

866
01:13:50,520 --> 01:13:51,920
No, no, that's okay.

867
01:13:54,960 --> 01:13:56,320
l hope you feel better.

868
01:14:00,640 --> 01:14:02,840
l could just show myself out.

869
01:14:03,359 --> 01:14:04,680
Thank you.

870
01:14:20,880 --> 01:14:22,600
She's gone, kid.

871
01:14:34,079 --> 01:14:35,800
Still high.

872
01:14:38,159 --> 01:14:40,720
We should tell him l'm sick.

873
01:14:42,159 --> 01:14:46,480
No, it's too soon.

874
01:14:46,800 --> 01:14:48,320
l don't think he's ready.

875
01:14:49,560 --> 01:14:51,920
l can call Susan
and tell her to bring some dinner.

876
01:14:52,079 --> 01:14:54,280
Don't worry about dinner, all right?

877
01:14:55,279 --> 01:14:56,880
Tom?

878
01:15:00,039 --> 01:15:02,000
lt's gonna be okay.

879
01:15:15,840 --> 01:15:17,680
Almost ready.

880
01:15:21,359 --> 01:15:25,200
And he wants to stay.
He needs us.

881
01:15:26,800 --> 01:15:29,880
So that's that.

882
01:15:30,560 --> 01:15:32,240
Yeah.

883
01:15:32,399 --> 01:15:36,080
-That's the craziest thing l've ever heard.
-l know.

884
01:15:37,039 --> 01:15:40,440
-l mean, really.
-Yeah, it's pretty bad.

885
01:15:54,880 --> 01:15:56,600
Good. Let it out.

886
01:16:04,039 --> 01:16:05,080
Get it up.

887
01:16:07,640 --> 01:16:10,640
That's all you gotta do. Ready?

888
01:16:10,840 --> 01:16:12,760
Simi Valley Police Station.

889
01:16:12,920 --> 01:16:15,240
Detective Crane, please.

890
01:16:21,319 --> 01:16:23,400
Detective Crane speaking.

891
01:16:24,479 --> 01:16:25,760
Hello?

892
01:16:26,239 --> 01:16:27,960
Hello?

893
01:16:28,399 --> 01:16:30,120
ls anyone there?

894
01:16:50,239 --> 01:16:54,440
-You have to go. l'll be fine.
-Let's not kid ourselves.

895
01:16:54,600 --> 01:16:57,800
Once they find out about the kid,
l'm out of a job. How many of these?

896
01:16:57,960 --> 01:17:03,160
Two. They're not gonna find out
about him. You have to testify.

897
01:17:05,800 --> 01:17:08,160
So you know for sure.

898
01:17:10,159 --> 01:17:12,080
l know l did the right thing.

899
01:17:13,560 --> 01:17:15,480
Then tell them.

900
01:17:16,239 --> 01:17:21,840
l don't want you to have any regrets,
Tom. Not because of me.

901
01:17:23,680 --> 01:17:25,680
No, honey, l won't.

902
01:17:26,159 --> 01:17:27,680
l'm gonna go with you.

903
01:17:27,840 --> 01:17:30,160
No, Meg. You're not well enough.

904
01:17:30,319 --> 01:17:33,040
Well, l'll feel worse if we don't go.

905
01:17:33,560 --> 01:17:35,240
What about the kid?

906
01:17:36,239 --> 01:17:38,480
We'll take him with us.

907
01:17:39,800 --> 01:17:42,160
We'll wait in the car.

908
01:17:45,199 --> 01:17:47,080
Oh, boy.

909
01:17:50,520 --> 01:17:51,880
All right.

910
01:17:53,560 --> 01:17:55,720
-Thanks a lot, N.B. l appreciate it.
-You bet.

911
01:17:55,880 --> 01:17:57,840
Ready for you, Tom.

912
01:17:58,159 --> 01:18:00,000
Hey, Otis.

913
01:18:00,960 --> 01:18:03,600
You're gonna be the sexiest accountant
in town.

914
01:18:19,600 --> 01:18:24,120
So this is an unofficial hearing, Tom,
and the goal of the proceedings...

915
01:18:24,279 --> 01:18:27,440
...is to determine if
an official investigation is necessary.

916
01:18:27,600 --> 01:18:29,080
-l understand.
-Okay.

917
01:18:29,239 --> 01:18:31,400
For the record,
were you the senior engineer.. .

918
01:18:31,560 --> 01:18:34,240
...on February 2nd,
the date of the fatal incident?

919
01:18:34,399 --> 01:18:35,400
l was.

920
01:18:35,560 --> 01:18:38,080
And could you describe for us
what happened that day...

921
01:18:38,239 --> 01:18:40,680
...to the best of your recollection?

922
01:18:40,840 --> 01:18:45,200
-l wish l could go in.
-Me too.

923
01:18:46,319 --> 01:18:47,760
Why do we have to hide?

924
01:18:49,199 --> 01:18:53,200
Why can't l just tell the social worker
l wanna stay with you?

925
01:18:54,319 --> 01:18:55,920
lt doesn't work like that.

926
01:18:56,800 --> 01:18:58,480
But why?

927
01:18:59,159 --> 01:19:02,560
People like to follow rules...

928
01:19:02,720 --> 01:19:07,720
...and you staying with us
definitely goes against that.

929
01:19:10,119 --> 01:19:13,440
And what was your first reaction
when you saw the car?

930
01:19:14,439 --> 01:19:15,640
l slowed the train down.

931
01:19:17,279 --> 01:19:19,920
But you didn't use
the emergency brake.

932
01:19:21,159 --> 01:19:25,200
l decided not to. The emergency brake
wouldn't have stopped that train in time.

933
01:19:25,359 --> 01:19:28,720
But your partner thinks
the impact might have been prevented.

934
01:19:29,279 --> 01:19:32,440
l disagree. At that speed,
with that many cars on the turn...

935
01:19:32,600 --> 01:19:34,360
.. .we probably would've derailed.

936
01:19:34,520 --> 01:19:38,480
lf you could do it all over again,
would you do anything differently?

937
01:19:43,159 --> 01:19:44,360
Mr. Stark.

938
01:19:48,000 --> 01:19:52,000
-l can't do it all over again.
-But if you could.

939
01:19:55,760 --> 01:19:57,120
No.

940
01:19:57,680 --> 01:19:59,840
l wouldn't have done
anything differently.

941
01:20:09,920 --> 01:20:11,080
lt's over, Tom.

942
01:20:11,520 --> 01:20:15,040
There's no official investigation.
Everything was by the book.

943
01:20:15,520 --> 01:20:16,800
Where you going?

944
01:20:16,960 --> 01:20:19,800
Hey, we got a streak schedule
for you tomorrow, Tom.

945
01:20:20,960 --> 01:20:23,200
Megan. Megan....

946
01:20:23,640 --> 01:20:26,680
-l didn't do anything.
-lt's okay. Get in the car. Get in the car.

947
01:20:26,840 --> 01:20:28,360
Honey. Meggie.

948
01:20:28,920 --> 01:20:31,160
-Honey.
-Megan.

949
01:20:31,319 --> 01:20:33,040
Megan.

950
01:20:35,960 --> 01:20:37,440
Megan.

951
01:20:53,680 --> 01:20:55,080
So...

952
01:20:56,239 --> 01:20:58,000
...Megan's sick.

953
01:20:58,800 --> 01:21:00,720
She's got cancer.

954
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:05,680
Can't they cure her?

955
01:21:07,439 --> 01:21:09,040
They did.

956
01:21:09,199 --> 01:21:10,920
Twice.

957
01:21:11,079 --> 01:21:12,600
lt came back.

958
01:21:13,319 --> 01:21:15,600
Can't they cure her again?

959
01:21:26,800 --> 01:21:28,880
ls Megan gonna die?

960
01:21:38,520 --> 01:21:40,240
Can l see her?

961
01:21:41,399 --> 01:21:43,960
Tom, she wants to go home.

962
01:22:23,319 --> 01:22:27,440
-Hey, listen. Thanks a lot.
-Of course.

963
01:22:27,600 --> 01:22:30,680
-Let me know if anything changes, okay?
-Yep.

964
01:22:32,600 --> 01:22:33,880
See you.

965
01:22:35,640 --> 01:22:38,560
-Drive safely.
-Yeah.

966
01:23:01,439 --> 01:23:04,720
Hey, hey, hey. Stop it. Stop it.
What are you doing?

967
01:23:04,880 --> 01:23:07,560
Hey, hey. Come here. Look at me.
Look at me. Look at me.

968
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:10,120
-What's going on? What's going on?
-Let go! Let go!

969
01:23:10,279 --> 01:23:11,760
-No!
-Hey, hey, hey.

970
01:23:11,920 --> 01:23:13,360
-Take it easy.
-l can't be here.

971
01:23:13,520 --> 01:23:16,240
-What? What are you talking about?
-l can't. l'm bad.

972
01:23:16,399 --> 01:23:18,480
You're ba-- What did you do?
What did you do?

973
01:23:18,920 --> 01:23:21,960
l told the principal
that my mom was dead.

974
01:23:22,119 --> 01:23:25,560
-You lied? Is that what you did?
-Yes. l shouldn't have.

975
01:23:25,720 --> 01:23:30,360
-God's punishing me. l killed her.
-What are you talking about?

976
01:23:30,520 --> 01:23:33,120
-She shouldn't have gone that day.
-No, no, no.

977
01:23:33,279 --> 01:23:35,960
-God's not punishing anybody.
-Megan is gonna die too now.

978
01:23:36,119 --> 01:23:38,200
Hey, look at me. Look at me.
Look at me.

979
01:23:38,359 --> 01:23:40,440
Megan was sick long before
you ever got here.

980
01:23:40,600 --> 01:23:45,960
-l shouldn't have let her out.
-No. Take it easy. Just take it easy.

981
01:23:46,119 --> 01:23:49,720
l was on the tracks, and l tried.
Mom.

982
01:23:49,880 --> 01:23:51,440
-Davey.
-Mom, l'm so sorry.

983
01:23:51,600 --> 01:23:55,400
-Davey.
-l shouldn't have let you die.

984
01:23:55,560 --> 01:23:57,520
lt's okay. It's all right. It's all right.

985
01:23:57,680 --> 01:24:00,040
-God is punishing me.
-No, you did the right thing.

986
01:24:00,199 --> 01:24:01,360
You did the right thing.

987
01:24:01,520 --> 01:24:06,840
Look. Listen to me.
It's okay. It's not your fault.

988
01:24:07,119 --> 01:24:09,320
-You di--
-Megan's dying now.

989
01:24:10,359 --> 01:24:15,160
-Because she's sick.
-No. God's punishing me.

990
01:24:15,439 --> 01:24:16,520
Easy, kid.

991
01:24:19,279 --> 01:24:22,200
lt's not your fault, okay?

992
01:25:38,600 --> 01:25:40,160
Here you go.

993
01:26:00,720 --> 01:26:02,760
Why don't you go see Megan now?

994
01:26:19,279 --> 01:26:21,520
Come sit by me.

995
01:26:33,239 --> 01:26:36,280
l wish we had more time.

996
01:26:38,359 --> 01:26:43,920
l would like to take care of you
a little bit longer.

997
01:26:47,720 --> 01:26:52,880
You know, if you think really hard,
maybe you could stay longer.

998
01:26:57,920 --> 01:27:00,880
l love you, Davey.

999
01:27:03,840 --> 01:27:06,080
And l will stay with you.

1000
01:27:06,560 --> 01:27:09,680
l will. Forever.

1001
01:27:10,800 --> 01:27:12,320
Right here.

1002
01:27:14,840 --> 01:27:17,320
l love you too, Megan.

1003
01:28:10,319 --> 01:28:13,160
-Promise.
-Anything.

1004
01:28:13,319 --> 01:28:19,040
To fight for him.
He is so much like you.

1005
01:28:23,039 --> 01:28:24,920
Whatever you want.

1006
01:28:27,119 --> 01:28:28,720
Promise.

1007
01:28:30,840 --> 01:28:32,520
l promise.

1008
01:29:14,920 --> 01:29:16,760
Oh, Meg.

1009
01:29:22,239 --> 01:29:23,720
She's gone.

1010
01:30:39,199 --> 01:30:40,800
Hey.

1011
01:30:40,960 --> 01:30:44,000
You remember that lady, Renee?

1012
01:30:44,239 --> 01:30:45,840
The social worker?

1013
01:30:46,279 --> 01:30:47,600
Yeah.

1014
01:30:48,600 --> 01:30:50,800
l think we need to go see her.

1015
01:30:51,439 --> 01:30:52,640
Why?

1016
01:30:53,960 --> 01:30:57,640
Well, you can't hide forever,
you know?

1017
01:30:57,800 --> 01:31:00,800
And you need to go to school...

1018
01:31:00,960 --> 01:31:04,720
...and be a kid again.

1019
01:31:07,560 --> 01:31:09,040
Hey, listen.

1020
01:31:09,359 --> 01:31:14,440
l want you to know
that whatever happens...

1021
01:31:14,960 --> 01:31:16,880
...we're in this together.

1022
01:31:19,479 --> 01:31:22,080
-Okay?
-Okay.

